<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 21 at 1:47PM CST  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...Dense Fog Along the Immediate Lake Michigan Shore...
Webcams and satellite imagery show that an area of dense fog is
hugging the immediate Cook County shoreline. Roads along the
lakefront could have sharply reduced visibility of one quarter
mile or less at times through mid afternoon. When driving in fog,
slow down, increase following distance, and use low beams.</description>
